 Handball XIV Africa Championship 2000 - Algeria |work=todor66.com |publisher=Todor Krastev |date=November 26, 2016 |accessdate= }}</ref>\n\n[[Egypt national handball team|Egypt]] finished first in the round robin tournament and wins its third African title. [[Algeria national handball team|Algeria]] finished second and [[Tunisia national handball team|Tunisia]] third.\n\n==Qualified teams==\n{{colbegin|colwidth=18em}}\n*{{hb|ALG}} ''{{small|(hosts)}}''\n*{{hb|CGO}}\n*{{hb|COD}}\n*{{hb|EGY}}\n*{{hb|GAB}}\n*{{hb|MAR}}\n*{{hb|TUN}}\n{{colend}}\n\n==Venues==\n*[[Hac\u00e8ne Harcha Arena]], [[Algiers]]\n*Omnisports Arena, [[Djasr Kasentina]] (Algiers)\n\n==Squads==\n{{Main article|2000 African Men's Handball Championship squads}}\n\n==Final tournament==\n===Matches===\n''All times are local ([[UTC+01:00|UTC+1]]).''\n\n{{handballbox\n|date    = 22 April 2000\n|time    = 15:30\n|team1   = {{hb-rt|ALG}}\n|score   = 32\u20138\n|team2   = {{hb|GAB}}\n|report  = \n|goals1  = \n|goals2  = \n|HT      = 15\u20133\n|twomin1 = \n|yellow1 = \n|red1    = \n|twomin2 = \n|yellow2 = \n|red2    = \n|stadium = [[Hac\u00e8ne Harcha Arena]], [[Algiers]]\n|referee = \n|refnat  = \n}}\n{{handballbox\n|date    = 23 April 2000\n|time    = 16:30\n|team1   = {{hb-rt|TUN}}\n|score   = 15\u201315\n|team2   = {{hb|MAR}}\n|report  = \n|goals1  = \n|goals2  = \n|HT      = 9\u20137\n|twomin1 = \n|yellow1 = \n|red1    = \n|twomin2 = \n|yellow2 = \n|red2    = \n|stadium = [[Hac\u00e8ne Harcha Arena]], [[Algiers]]\n|referee = \n|refnat  = \n}}\n{{handballbox\n|date    = 23 April 2000\n|time    = 16:30\n|team1   = {{hb-rt|EGY}}\n|score   = 35\u201318\n|team2   = {{hb|CGO}}\n|report  = \n|goals1  = \n|goals2  = \n|HT      = 18\u20138\n|twomin1 = \n|yellow1 = \n|red1    = \n|twomin2 = \n|yellow2 = \n|red2    = \n|stadium = Omnisports Arena, [[Djasr Kasentina]] (Algiers)\n|referee = \n|refnat  = \n}}\n----\n{{handballbox\n|date    = 24 April 2000\n|time    = 14:30\n|team1   = {{hb-rt|TUN}}\n|score   = 51\u20