{"title_page": "Soil organic carbon", "text_new": "Soil organic carbon (SOC) is one part\u00a0 [[Soil carbon]] in the much larger global carbon cycle that involves the cycling of carbon through the soil, vegetation, ocean and the atmosphere.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.fao.org/3/a-i6937e.pdf|title=FAO 2017. Soil Organic Carbon: the hidden potential. Food and Agriculture Organization of the United NationsRome, Italy|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=April 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe SOC pool stores an estimated 1 500 PgC (Petagrams of carbon) in the first meter of soil,which is more carbon than is contained in the atmosphere (roughly 800 PgC) andterrestrial vegetation (500 PgC) combined. This phenomenal SOC reservoir is not static, but is constantly cycling between the different global carbon pools in various molecularforms <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sustainableagriculture.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Soil_C_review_Kane_Dec_4-final-v4.pdf|title=Carbon Sequestration Potential on Agricultural Lands A Review of CurrentScience and Available Practices|last=Kane|first=Daniel|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>.\n", "text_old": "Soil organic carbon (SOC) is one part in the much larger global carbon cycle that involves the cycling of carbon through the soil, vegetation, ocean and the atmosphere<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.fao.org/3/a-i6937e.pdf|title=FAO 2017. Soil Organic Carbon: the hidden potential. Food and Agriculture Organization of the United NationsRome, Italy|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=April 3, 2020}}</ref>.\n\nThe SOC pool stores an estimated 1 500 PgC (Petagrams of carbon) in the first meter of soil,which is more carbon than is contained in the atmosphere (roughly 800 PgC) andterrestrial vegetation (500 PgC) combined. This phenomenal SOC reservoir is not static, but is constantly cycling between the different global carbon pools in various molecularforms <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sustainableagriculture.net/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Soil_C_review_Kane_Dec_4-final-v4.pdf|title=Carbon Sequestration Potential on Agricultural Lands A Review of CurrentScience and Available Practices|last=Kane|first=Daniel|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>.\n", "name_user": "Ninojosewikipedista", "label": "safe", "comment": "link soil carbon", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soil_organic_carbon"}
