al Performances |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=June 2000 |website=Interlochen Center for the Arts |publisher=Northern Michigan Connection |accessdate=17 December 2017 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20000824143519/http://www.michiweb.com/interlochen/news/perform.html |archivedate=2000-08-24 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n:{{note label|CSF|N|N}}This concert was a part of the \"[[Colorado State Fair]]\"\n:{{note label|BUM|O|O}}This concert was a part of \"[[Bumbershoot]]\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thestranger.com/seattle/the-strangers-bumbershoot-guide/Content?oid=4787 |title=The Stranger's Bumbershoot Guide |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=31 August 2000 |website=[[The Stranger (newspaper)|The Stranger]] |publisher= |accessdate=17 December 2017}}</ref>\n:{{note label|LSD|P|P}}This concert was a part of the \"Last Chance Summer Dance\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.z100portland.com:80/events/lcsd00/ |title=Z100's Last Chance Summer Dance 2000 |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=August 2000 |website=[[KKRZ]] |publisher=[[iHeartMedia|Clear Channel Communications]] |accessdate=17 December 2017 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20000901234259/http://www.z100portland.com/events/lcsd00/ |archivedate=2000-09-01 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n{{div col end}}\n\n;Cancellations and rescheduled shows\n{| cellpadding=\"2\" style=\"border:0 solid darkgrey; font-size:90%\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:150px;\"| <!--Date-->\n! style=\"width:200px;\"| <!--Location-->\n! style=\"width:300px;\"| <!--Venue-->\n! style=\"width:625px;\"| <!--Reason/Additional Info-->\n|- border=\"0\"\n|-\n|14 July 2000\n|Augusta, Georgia\n|[[James Brown Arena|Augusta-Richmond County Civic Center]]\n|Moved to Fort Gordon\n|-\n|14 August 2000\n|Midland, Michigan\n|[[Midland Center for the Arts]]\n|Moved to the Midland County Fair Grandstand\n|-\n|3 September 2000\n|Portland, Oregan\n|[[Portland Meadows]]\n|Moved to the Tom McCall Waterfront Park\n|-\n|28 November 2000\n|[[Berlin]], Germany\n|Postbahnhof\n|Moved to Columbiahalle\n|-\n|29 November 2000\n|[[Prague]], [[Czech Republic]]\n|[[:cs:Zimn\u00ed stadion Eden|Zimn\u00ed stadion Eden]]\n|Cancelled\n|-\n|30 November 2000\n|[[Vienna]], [[Austria]]\n|Libro Music Hall\n|Cancelled\n|-\n|}\n\n==Personnel==\n;Band\n*Drums: Karl Lewis\n*Guitar: [[Ben Carey]] and Daniel Jones\n*Bass guitar: Lee Novak\n*Keyboards: [[Jennifer Blakeman]] and Daniel Jones\n*Backing vocalists: Angela Bekker, [[Elisa Fiorillo]] and Anna Maria La Spina\n\n;Crew\n*Tour manager: Peter McFee\n**Assistant tour manager: Susie Steadman\n*Stage manager: Colin Skals\n*Wardrobe: Nina De Palma\n*Production design: Willy Williams and Bruce Ramus\n*Lighting director: Bruce Ramus\n**Lighting operator: Sean Hackett\n*FOH Engineer: Colin Ellis\n*Monitor engineer: Scott Pike\n*Guitar technician: Adrian Dessent and Lindsay McKay\n*Drum technician: Simon Moran\n\n==External links==\n*[http://savagegarden.com/ Savage Garden Official Website]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Savage Garden}}\n\n[[Category:2000 concert tours]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox concert\n| concert_tour_name = Affirmation World Tour\n| image             = SavageGarden_2000TourPoster.jpg\n| image_size        = 220px\n| landscape         = \n| alt               = \n| caption           = Promotional poster for the tour\n| artist            = [[Savage Garden]]\n| album             = ''[[Affirmation (Savage Garden album)|Affirmation]]''\n| start_date        = {{Start date|2000|04|02|df=yes}}\n| end_date          = {{End date|2000|12|17|df=yes}}\n| number_of_legs    = 4\n| number_of_shows   = 7 in Asia<br>16 in Australia<br>37 in North America<br>21 in Europe<br>3 in Africa<br>84 Total\n| last_tour         = Future Of Earthly Delites Tour<br>(1998)\n| this_tour         = Affirmation World Tour<br>(2000)\n| next_tour         = \n| misc              = \n}}\n\nThe '''Affirmation World Tour''' is the third and final concert tour by Australian group, [[Savage Garden]]. The tour was launched to support their second studio album, ''[[Affirmation (Savage Garden album)|Affirmation]]'' (1999). The tour played over 80 shows in [[Asia]], [[Australia (continent)|Australia]], [[North America]], [[Europe]] and [[Africa]].\n\nConcerts in [[Brisbane]] were recorded and released to video in 2001. ''[[Superstars and Cannonballs]]'' includes concert footage and the documentary, \"Parallel Lines\" and music videos.\n\n==Opening acts==\n*[[Vanessa Amorosi]] {{small|(Australia)}}\n*[[Kina (musician)|Kina]] {{small|(North America)}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2000/07/23/style/one-foot-in-motown-one-in-led-zeppelin.html |title=One Foot in Motown, One in Led Zeppelin |last1=Century |first1=Douglas |last2= |first2= |date=23 July 2000 |website=[[The New York Times]] |publisher=[[The New York Times Company]] |accessdate=17 December 2017}}</ref>\n*[[S.O.A.P. (band)|S.O.A.P.]] {{small|(Europe)}}\n\n==Setlist==\nThe following setlist was obtained from the 8 December 2000 concert, held at the Point Theatre in Dublin, Ireland. It does not represent all concerts for the duration of the tour.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.irishtimes.com/news/savage-garden-point-theatre-1.1120471 |title=Savage Garden - Point Theatre |last1=Smith |first1=Laura |last2= |first2= |date=11 December 2000 |website=[[The Irish Times]] |publisher= |accessdate=17 December 2017}}</ref>\n\n#\"The Best Thing\"\n#\"[[Break Me Shake Me]]\"\n#\"[[To the Moon and Back (Savage Garden song)|To the Moon and Back]]\"\n#\"The Lover After Me\"\n#\"I Don't Know You Anymore\"\n#\"Santa Monica\"\n#\"Two Beds and a Coffee Machine\"\n#\"You Can Still Be Free\"\n#\"[[The Animal Song]]\"\n#\"Hold Me\"\n#\"Gunning Down Romance\"\n#\"[[Crash and Burn (Savage Garden song)|Crash and Burn]]\"\n#\"[[Truly Madly Deeply]]\"\n#\"Chained to You\"\n#\"[[I Want You (Savage Garden song)|I Want You]]\"\n#\"[[I Knew I Loved You (Savage Garden song)|I Knew I Loved You]]\"\n#\"[[Affirmation (Savage Garden song)|Affirmation]]\"\n\n==Tour dates==\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:150px;\"|Date\n! style=\"width:150px;\"|City\n! style=\"width:150px;\"|Country\n! style=\"width:250px;\"|Venue\n|-\n! colspan=\"4\"|Asia\n|-\n|2 April 2000\n|[[Tokyo]]\n|rowspan=\"7\"|[[Japan]]\n|[[NHK Hall]]\n|-\n|4 April 2000\n|[[Yokohama]]\n|[[:ja:\u795e\u5948\u5ddd\u770c\u7acb\u770c\u6c11\u30db\u30fc\u30eb|Kanagawa Prefectural Hall]]\n|-\n|5 April 2000\n|Tokyo\n|NHK Hall\n|-\n|7 April 2000\n|[[Fukuoka]]\n|[[Fukuoka Sunpalace]]\n|-\n|8 April 2000\n|[[Osaka]]\n|[[Orix Theater|K\u014dsei Nenkin Kaikan]]\n|-\n|10 April 2000\n|[[Nagoya]]\n|[[Aichi K\u014dsei Nenkin Kaikan]]\n|-\n|12 April 2000\n|Tokyo\n|[[Tokyo International Forum]]\n|-\n! colspan=\"4\"|Australia\n|-\n|28 April 2000\n|[[Cairns]]\n|rowspan=\"16\"|[[Australia]]\n|[[Cairns Convention Centre|CCC Great Hall]]\n|-\n|29 April 2000\n|[[Townsville]]\n|[[Townsville Entertainment and Convention Centre|Townsville Entertainment Centre]]\n|-\n|1 May 2000\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Melbourne]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Rod Laver Arena]]\n|-\n|2 May 2000\n|-\n|4 May 2000\n|[[Adelaide]]\n|[[Adelaide Entertainment Centre]]\n|-\n|6 May 2000\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Perth]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Perth Entertainment Centre]]\n|-\n|7 May 2000\n|-\n|10 May 2000\n|[[Canberra]]\n|[[Canberra Theatre]]\n|-\n|13 May 2000\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Sydney]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Sydney Entertainment Centre]]\n|-\n|14 May 2000\n|-\n|16 May 2000\n|[[Newcastle, New South Wales|Newcastle]]\n|[[Newcastle Entertainment Centre]]\n|-\n|17 May 2000\n|[[Wollongong]]\n|[[WIN Entertainment Centre|Wollongong Entertainment Centre]]\n|-\n|20 May 2000\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Brisbane]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Brisbane Entertainment Centre]]\n|-\n|21 May 2000\n|-\n|24 May 2000\n|[[Launceston, Tasmania|Launceston]]\n|[[Silverdome (Launceston)|Silverdome]]\n|-\n|25 May 2000\n|[[Hobart]]\n|[[Derwent Entertainment Centre]]\n|-\n! colspan=\"4\"|North America<ref>{{cite